The paper deals with the computational complexity of bisimilarity checking on infinite state systems, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. The use of partition refinement approach and the focus on branching bisimilarity suggest that the paper may belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The paper also deals with formal languages and automata, which are topics in Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) and Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The use of techniques for handling infinite state systems suggests that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper presents a new algorithm for bisimilarity checking, which may be of interest to researchers in Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
